<TITLE> BNP reform to start on grassroot reports: Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 21 (bdnews24.com) - BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia said Saturday her party's reform would start soon after the divisional reports of grassroots interviews were reviewed by the standing committee. "We'll soon begin party restructuring after reviewing all six reports," Khaleda told reporters after receiving reports from Dhaka, Rajshahi and Khulna divisions at her Gulshan office in the evening. The Chittagong division report was submitted Wednesday. "The party standing committee will review all the reports after we receive the remaining reports from the remaining two divisions - Barisal and Sylhet," the BNP chief said. Khaleda, leader of the opposition in parliament, formed six organising committees headed by six party joint secretary-generals on Feb 1 to report on the situation at the grassroots. Joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan said reports prepared through interviews with local-level leaders between Feb 3-24 would be discussed at the standing committee meeting. The former premier announced on Jan 1 that her party would be reformed at level
